  "text": "[4] Weber et al. [1997, 1998 ] hypothesize that a third species, possibly ammonia, might be involved in the nucleation mechanism, which would explain the deviation between the bimolecular theory and measurements. [CITATION_1] showed that atmospheric mixing processes such as entrainment might produce a substantial enhancement of the nucleation rate. Part of the discrepancy may also be caused by the fact that classical nucleation theory is based on thermodynamic bulk properties, which is not realistic for the very small critical clusters that can not be classified as being in the liquid phase [Preining, 1998 ].",
